WIFI-JAMMER-2026 is a powerful stand-alone Windows application for WiFi security testing and network analysis. Unlike traditional Linux-based tools that require complex setup, this executable brings professional-grade deauthentication attacks to Windows with a clean command-line interface and automated monitor mode configuration [citation:1].

The tool follows SOLID architecture principles with multiple attack types including Deauth, Disassoc, Beacon Flood, and Auth Flood attacks. It features automatic network discovery, real-time scanning, and beautiful terminal output with progress bars and color-coded tables [citation:1].

Designed for security researchers and penetration testers, this tool provides comprehensive WiFi assessment capabilities while maintaining clean, maintainable code structure and easy one-command installation [citation:1].

