    ╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
    ║                    🔧 HOW DEAUTH ATTACK WORKS                         ║
    ╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
    
    A deauthentication attack sends forged deauthentication packets from your machine to a client connected to the target network. These packets include fake sender addresses that make them appear to the client as if they were sent from the access point itself [citation:3].
    
    Upon receipt of such packets, most clients disconnect from the network and immediately try to reconnect — but repeatedly fail to establish connection as long as the attack continues. This creates an effective denial-of-service condition [citation:3].
    
    The tool supports both targeted attacks (specific client) and broadcast attacks (all clients on network).

