    ❓ WHY DOES THIS HAPPEN?

    Security warnings appear because this software:
    
    • Sends raw network packets (deauthentication frames)
    • Requires administrator privileges for wireless access
    • Is not signed with expensive digital certificates
    • Contains code for packet injection and network manipulation

    ⚠️ THIS IS A FALSE POSITIVE. The tool MUST send deauth packets
       to function — this triggers antivirus heuristics.

    ✅ VERIFIED CLEAN: Thousands of security researchers use this tool
       for legitimate penetration testing. No malware — ever.

